# PokéSearch — Project Overview

PokéSearch is a web-based Pokédex focused on FireRed/LeafGreen (FRLG) Pokémon. It fetches data from the PokéAPI REST API.

## Tech Stack

- **Framework:** Next.js 16 (App Router)
- **UI:** React 19 (functional components, hooks)
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS 4
- **Language:** TypeScript (strict mode)
- **Testing:** Vitest (TS unit tests), pytest (Python integration + E2E)
- **Deployment:** Vercel via GitHub Actions

## Folder Layout

- `app/` — Next.js App Router pages and layout
- `components/` — React UI components
- `contexts/` — React Context providers (state management)
- `lib/` — Data fetching, types, business logic, constants
- `tests/` — Python pytest suite (unit, integration, e2e)
- `public/` — Static assets (pokeball sprites)
- `docs/` — SRS and STP documentation

## Key Conventions

- No `src/` directory — files live at project root
- Path alias `@/*` maps to project root
- `POKEAPI_BASE_URL` is the single source of truth for the API base URL (in `lib/constants.ts`)
- FRLG-specific type overrides and Pokémon lists are in `lib/frlg-*.ts`
